            <title>[SPARK-32115] Incorrect results for SUBSTRING when overflow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32115</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SQL query SELECT SUBSTRING(&quot;abc&quot;, -1207959552, -1207959552) incorrectly returns &quot;abc&quot; against expected output of &quot;&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
 This is a result of integer overflow in addition&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/8c44d744631516a5cdaf63406e69a9dd11e5b878/common/unsafe/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/unsafe/types/UTF8String.java#L345&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/8c44d744631516a5cdaf63406e69a9dd11e5b878/common/unsafe/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/unsafe/types/UTF8String.java#L345&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
